<emphasis box="[247,432,2156,2194]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="85">Peraeopod</emphasis>
4: merus short, not expanded posteriorly. 
<emphasis box="[247,432,2201,2240]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="85">Peraeopod</emphasis>
5: coxa in femqle subequal or larger than in male, without fringe of long setae; dactylus with large unguis and 1-2 small accessory spines. 
<emphasis box="[987,1224,2293,2332]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="85">Peraeopod 6:</emphasis>
dactylus with large unguis and 2 small accessory spines. 
<emphasis box="[247,432,2385,2423]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="85">Peraeopod</emphasis>
7: dactylus with large unguis and 1-2 small accessory spines. 
<emphasis box="[573,714,2431,2469]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="85">Pleopod</emphasis>
2: inner ramus reduced, 1Â­ articulate or pleopod uniramous. 
<emphasis box="[818,960,2477,2515]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="85">Pleopod</emphasis>
